Let $A$ and $B$ be the times at which Alice and Bob arrive, respectively.  Then $(A,B)$ can be any point in the square with vertices $(1,1),$ $(1,2),$ $(2,1),$ and $(2,2).$  The set of points for which Alice arrives after Bob is the set of points below the line $y = x.$

[asy]
